title: Make D3.Selection.datum generic so that return values have type
body:
I added a generic version of `D3.Selection.datum`:

``` TypeScript
<T>(): T;
```

Since `datum()` can return any type of data stored with the element, when we need to use the data returned by it, we first need to cast it into a type in TypeScript:

``` TypeScript
console.log((<ISomeType>selection.datum()).foo().bar("bla", bla));
```

This is tedious and not readable.

Instead we can add the generic signature, so it's easier to use the return value of datum with type:

``` TypeScript
console.log(selection.datum<ISomeType>().foo().bar("bla", bla));
```

Also added some comments from the [doc](https://github.com/mbostock/d3/wiki/Selections#datum).

title: Fix ErrnoException `errno` type
body:
It's a number (technically an integer) in all Node API versions that have a corresponding .d.ts file here.

Relevant lines:

https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.8.8-release/src/node.cc#L769-L806
https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.10.1-release/src/node.cc#L750
https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.11.13-release/src/node.cc#L752
https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.12.0-release/src/node.cc#L762

I added the ErrnoException type to the Node 0.8.8 .d.ts file, since it did, in fact, exist with the same interface then (This has actually been the case [since at least 0.4](https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.4/src/node.cc#L1022-L1063)).

title: Update angular.d.ts - Fix for $q.all() method
body:
Method $q.all() supports passing promises both as array and as hash, and return type is dependent of argument.
Previously the argument type could be either array and hash, but return type was always a promise of array. So it was splitted into two overloads.
